          <name>VISUAL_FITTING_MODE</name>
          <initializer>= OPACITY + 1</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The fitting mode of the visual. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;fittingMode&quot;, type <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1FittingMode" kindref="compound">FittingMode</ref> (Property::INTEGER) or Property::STRING. <simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelVisual_1abbf3658ac17aaf73389c6e6b39b62585" kindref="member">DevelVisual::FittingMode</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>The default is defined by the type of visual (if it&apos;s suitable to be stretched or not). </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelVisual_1_1Property_1a198754e8723ad8b288f0326d356b587bae7c08cc534e6ef219cbd4b52dce94841" prot="public">
          <name>CORNER_RADIUS</name>
          <initializer>= OPACITY + 2</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The radius for the rounded corners of the visual. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;cornerRadius&quot;, type Property::FLOAT or Property::VECTOR4, animatable <simplesect kind="note"><para>By default, it is Vector::ZERO. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Only Property::Vector4 can be animated. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Each radius will clamp internally to the half of smaller of the visual width and visual height. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Their may exist some alias when you use it as ClippingMode::CLIP_CHILDREN. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Radius value are used in clockwise order from top-left-corner to bottom-left-corner. When radius is Vector4(x, y, z, w) x y +<ndash/>+ | | +<ndash/>+ w z </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelVisual_1_1Property_1a198754e8723ad8b288f0326d356b587bacafc7ba7ab215aa15ecb6873f58ebcfe" prot="public">
          <name>CORNER_RADIUS_POLICY</name>
          <initializer>= OPACITY + 3</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether the corner radius value is relative (percentage [0.0f to 0.5f] of the visual size) or absolute (in world units). </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;cornerRadiusPolicy&quot;, type Property::INTEGER. <simplesect kind="see"><para>Policy::Type </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>By default, it is ABSOLUTE to the visual&apos;s size. If it is RELATIVE, the corner radius value is relative to the smaller of the visual width and visual height. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelVisual_1_1Property_1a198754e8723ad8b288f0326d356b587ba0f22b704df756c0ce179ca97e63be980" prot="public">
