</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelVisual_1_1Property_1a198754e8723ad8b288f0326d356b587baea64dc58689c65e5b90f65b7d6bd839f" prot="public">
          <name>BORDERLINE_OFFSET</name>
          <initializer>= OPACITY + 6</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The offset from the visual borderline (recommend [-1.0f to 1.0f]). </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;borderlineOffset&quot;, type Property::FLOAT, animatable <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default value is 0.0f. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This value will clamp internally to [-1.0f to 1.0f]. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelVisual_1_1Property_1a198754e8723ad8b288f0326d356b587ba9e7e01594cf320cbf6b7ea949ff1c94b" prot="public">
          <name>CORNER_SQUARENESS</name>
          <initializer>= OPACITY + 7</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The squareness for the rounded corners of the visual. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;cornerSquareness&quot;, type Property::FLOAT or Property::VECTOR4, animatable <simplesect kind="note"><para>By default, it is Vector::ZERO. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Each squareness will clamp internally as [0.0 1.0]. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Squareness value are used in clockwise order from top-left-corner to bottom-left-corner. When squareness is Vector4(x, y, z, w) x y +<ndash/>+ | | +<ndash/>+ w z </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
